etymology.description: 十(十) (shí, "ten") + 十(十) (shí, "ten") with a connecting stroke -> variant of 廿(廿) (niàn, "twenty")
etymology.interpretation: 卄(卄) (niàn, "twenty") is a variant form of 廿(廿) (niàn, "twenty"), which visually combines two 十(十) (shí, "ten") characters with a horizontal stroke to represent the concept of 'twenty'.
